cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.ET, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of RISCAL in teaching courses on logic and formal methods. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as RISCAL is a language for formal modeling of theories and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses enhancements to the RISCAL tool, such as automatic generation of checkable verification conditions and visualization of procedure execution. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possibility as RISCAL is a relatively new tool for educational purposes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the correctness of algorithms in RISCAL.
